President Biden addressed a group of labor union leaders at the White House, expressing his commitment to supporting unions and workers. He praised the essential workers who have played a crucial role during the COVID-19 crisis and highlighted the importance of treating all workers with dignity. He emphasized the need to build back the economy better than before, with a focus on creating good jobs, raising wages, and providing benefits and protections for workers. President Biden also discussed his administration's efforts to promote worker organizing and employment, including the creation of a task force and the push for the PRO Act. He called for government support for unions and the removal of barriers to organizing. The President outlined his plans for infrastructure investment and the expansion of social programs, such as affordable housing, healthcare, and education. He also emphasized the importance of addressing climate change and creating a more sustainable economy. President Biden concluded by expressing his gratitude for the labor movement and its contributions to the country.